Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamic study of 2-methyl-tetrahydrofuran with isomeric chlorobutanes
Citation.sAbstract: Excess molar volumes, VE, isentropic compressibility deviations, DeS, and excess molar enthalpies, HE, for the binary mixtures 2-methyltetrahydrofuran with 1-chlorobutane, 2-chlorobutane, 2-methyl-1-chloropropane and 2-methyl-2-chloropropane have been determined at temperatures 298.15 and 313.15 K, excess molar enthalpies were only measured at 298.15 K.We have applied the Prigogine Flory Patterson (PFP) theory to these mixtures at 298.15 K.
